cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper proposes a method for optimizing the architecture of deep learning models, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs), by using PCA to analyze the activations of each layer and the dimensionality of the space described by the filters generating these activations. This work is primarily focused on improving the efficiency of CNNs, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. Additionally, the use of PCA for dimensionality reduction is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the optimization of CNN architecture is related to the field of software engineering (cs.SD).
